[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating display options in CI**\n\nI'm thinking about issues with display in CI since there's a chance it could hang or fail. I wonder if using Xvfb might work, but that’s a no. There's the option of using `Unsafe.allocateInstance(RunnerJFrame)`, but reflection and unsafe seems worse. I’m considering whether MethodHandles would involve direct reflection to public constructors. I notice many existing tests using this for inner dynamic classes, but the guidance says no direct reflection unless public API requires it.\n\n**Evaluating image loading**\n\nI need to handle the fact that there's no GUI available. I might need to ensure that all icons are loaded and that their width and height are greater than zero. I'm wondering if the GIF image loading is asynchronous while the ImageIcon with a URL loads synchronously? It likely uses Toolkit and MediaTracker, so I should check if getIconWidth is greater than or equal to zero to be sure everything's functioning as it should!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_08953fcd1000c0ed0169fa713d0bc4819db6e0c159c7ba7122\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp-nFR4QyP6YN6-HV2x3dF2bJcazg59f3r4P_Ovhvv_OTh7rF1gXuS9PJDKCycqDSw6uboUkhTjuTeFifljrMz1jdffLrqnHHE_8tmZONfZPwBD5BHlv_kKQgwKkpIuaT912iNMfLV95xlZ7QeHKf1Tz0RCKhRb-ep-RHQVUluBGLRUJeDSlVi6T_PcO489BAhWkpREtN4es6ymeHY2AMkwPrSWgXz8GTaShzbMmmUs_HHLhjuLvd88usauT8Okq-Qrf-hWCLXLL5JdT6TYuSE3pioHsm_9uZTcvzdvgD1AeIB0K0ZHMxXKtlBmHVgO0lDEkzeGmxTb3uEfeOeCdhfNDiGdKDbm1pj2fjC01aW97eAZXUt6VUQUNbIVksco5u0_rMkShufzSdVUAyx_QSI-4b6iJMh1EIQ8hphgbEJVzYo9ueKxRMhdW2evvNKcJh5Ov8biasVhWWj8l87bCl7JdfGGund9-2AQl51qJXTai30qoFO8DZKsYLyr4Wgyk-SEEwT6YLPxqo0An7tKezBVptI31U6rkM1eJQJLAzCrbyn-S-3E9SDjXVdIz_C0Us_n8fbx4MqIwXVUhibgSKserx0_NvcBCjdmo0QPjezHVR-SXXgImvVovJXJAHs9f11VfMSQHrl_m4v2S1DWndlEFuh4yOSwz2dl9JpKNJ3jIgVfHZfmZPpxevosnuUuQSm4C3lK8VN-f2LOM35i8MfIb2Iwp-RqAncdtda-F2-lZIiIU83gl4jSi