r. \\n\\nI'm thinking about avoiding reflection by using a different package but realize that dynamic reflection could be unsupported without the right config. I need to check if the agent generated the reflection metadata when executing tests on the JVM first. It seems like the classloader's resource calls might integrate external data into metadata, which is a good approach since we're not modifying the config.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Planning test implementation**\\n\\nI think I need a user-code filter that excludes the test package but includes the library. This way, the agent can successfully record resource calls from the library, which seems like a solid approach. I’m feeling good about this direction. Now, it's time to write the test. I want to make sure I'm thorough so that I capture any potential issues. Let's get started on that!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_kSm9CKcuAHHWcCyFJ0qu3WX9|fc_08953fcd1000c0ed0169fa71996428819db94ad9a62db6dee8", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.scalatest/scalatest-core_3/3.2.19/src/test/scala/org_scalatest/scalatest_core_3/IconEmbellishedListCellRendererInnerIconsTest.scala", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_scalatest.scalatest_core_3\n\nimport java.lang.reflect.Constructor\nimport java.lang.reflect.Method\n\nimport javax.swing.ImageIcon\n\nimport org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test\n\nclass IconEmbellishedListCellRendererInnerIconsTest {\n\n  @Test\n  def initializesEveryRendererIconResource(): Unit = {\n    val rendererClass: Class[?] = Class.forName(\"org.scalatest.tools.IconEmbellishedListCellRenderer\")\n    val renderer: Object = rendererClass.getConstructor().newInstance().asInstanceOf[Object]\n    val iconsClass: Class[?] = Class.forName(\"org.scalatest.tools.IconEmbellishedListCellRenderer$Icons$\")\n    val iconsConstructor: Constructor[?] = iconsClass.getConstructor(rendererClass)\n    val icons: Object = iconsConstructor.newInstance(renderer).asInstanceOf[Object]\n\n    val iconResources: Map[String, String] = Map(\n      \"testStartingIcon\" -> \"purpledot.gif\",\n      \"testSucceededIcon\" -> \"greendot.gif\",\n      \"testFailedIcon\" -> \"reddot.gif\",\n      \"infoProvidedIcon\" -> \"bluedot.gif\",\n      \"runStartingIcon\" -> \"graydot.gif\",\n      \"suiteStartingIcon\" -> \"cyandot.gif\",\n      \"testIgnoredIcon\" -> \"yellowdot.gif\",\n      \"testStartingSelIcon\" -> \"purpledotsel.gif\",\n      \"testSucceededSelIcon\" -> \"greendotsel.gif\",\n      \"testFailedSelIcon\" -> \"reddotsel.gif\",\n      \"infoProvidedSelIcon\" -> \"bluedotsel.gif\",\n      \"runStartingSelIcon\" -> \"graydotsel.gif\",\n      \"suiteStartingSelIcon\" -> \"cyandotsel.gif\",\n      \"testIgnoredSelIcon\" -> \"yellowdotsel.gif\"\n    )\n\n    iconResources.foreach { case (methodName: String, resourceName: String) =>\n      val method: Method = iconsClass.getMethod(methodName)\n      val icon: ImageIcon = method.invoke(icons).asInstanceOf[ImageIcon]\n\n      assertThat(icon.getDescription()).endsWith(s\"images/$resourceName\")\n      assertThat(icon.getIconWidth()).isGreaterThan(0)\n      assertThat(icon.getIconHeight()).isGreaterThan(0)\n    }\n  }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 416, "output": 2122, "cacheRead": 28672, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 31210, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778020738408, "responseId": "resp_08953fcd1000c0ed0169fa7182f590819d9df852d31db8f999"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_kSm9CKcuAHHWcCyFJ0qu3WX9|fc_08953fcd1000c0ed0169fa71996428819db94ad9a62db6dee8", "toolName": "write", "content": [{"type"