tead, keeping everything organized without reflection issues. Would adding Java conflict with the Gradle Scala plugin?\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating Java helper usage**\\n\\nI'm considering whether using a Java helper counts as a \\\"test file.\\\" Reviewers might not like it, and using direct reflection could be against the rules. The developer emphasized avoiding direct reflection in tests unless public APIs require it. Using a Java helper sidesteps reflection but relies on a private class at compile time. It's okay to keep tests outside library packages, so I'll create a package-private helper under `src/test/java`. I need to make sure this doesn't violate mapping between report classes and test class files, and check if javac syntax supports that format.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering Java and Scala integration**\\n\\nI'm thinking about whether the source compiler might refuse the import due to the binary name having a `$`. This could be a potential issue because the `IconEmbellishedListCellRenderer` class is public in bytecode but has a private Scala signature, which javac will ignore — good to know! It might be better to replace Scala test reflections with a Java helper. I'll need Java for that. The Scala test file must still include assertions. Should the Java helper return a `Map` to eliminate Scala-Java collection conversions or perhaps use a static method like `loadIcon(String accessor)` instead?\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering Java and Scala integration**\\n\\nI'm thinking about whether methods could be public to simplify things, or if a nested class should be package-private. I wonder if the method return type is accessible. I need to import library classes in Java and question if Java will compile if I import private Scala classes directly. This might help avoid reflection and keep direct class references, which is important for the Native Image. I plan to edit the Scala test to remove reflection.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_Sk4OjUmWbClUpv9yNtVhnkfX|fc_08953fcd1000c0ed0169fa71d97a48819d938212ee66dd21fc", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.scalatest/scalatest-core_3/3.2.19/src/test/java/org_scalatest/scalatest_core_3/IconEmbellishedListCellRendererInnerIconsAccess.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_scalatest.scalatest_core_3;\n\nimport java.util.Arrays;\nimport java.util.List;\nimport javax.swing.ImageIcon;\nimport org.scalatest.tools.IconEmbellishedListCellRenderer;\nimport org.scalatest.tools.IconEmbellishedListCellRenderer$Icons$;\n\nfinal class IconEmbellishedListCellRendererInnerIconsAccess {\n    private IconEmbellishedListCellRendererInnerIconsAccess() {\n    }\n\n    static List<IconResource> loadPrimaryIcons() {\n        IconEmbellishedListCellRenderer renderer = new IconEmbellishedListCellRenderer();\n        IconEmbellishedListCellRenderer$Icons$ icons = new IconEmbellishedListCellRenderer$Icons$(renderer);\n        return Arrays.asList(\n                new IconResource(\"images/purpledot.gif\", icons.testStartingIcon()),\n                new IconResource(\"images/greendot.gif\", icons.testSucceededIcon()),\n                new IconResource(\"images/reddot.gif\", icons.testFailedIcon()),\n                new IconResource(\"images/bluedot.gif\", icons.infoProvidedIcon()),\n                new IconResource(\"images/graydot.gif\", icons.runStartingIcon()),\n                new IconResource(\"images/cyandot.gif\", icons.suiteStartingIcon()),\n                new IconResource(\"images/yellowdot.gif\", icons.testIgnoredIcon()),\n                new IconResource(\"images/purpledotsel.gif\", icons.testStartingSelIcon()),\n                new IconResource(\"images/greendotsel.gif\", icons.testSucceededSelIcon(